24/05/2005
VATICAN CITY, Vatican -- Bulgarian President Georgi Parvanov met with Pope Benedict XVI on Monday (23 May), becoming the first East European head of state to do so. 
Parvanov, in Rome for activities marking the Day of the Bulgarian and Slavic Letters, also extended an official invitation to the pontiff to visit Bulgaria.
Also Monday, Bulgarian Finance Minister Milen Velchev visited Belgrade, meeting with Serbian counterpart Mladjan Dinkic and President Boris Tadic. 
Velchev reaffirmed Sofia's support for efforts by Serbia-Montenegro to move towards EU accession. 
(Trud, 24 Chasa, Monitor - 24/05/05; bTV - 23/05/05)
